{{italic title}} {{Infobox book series | name = Problems, Problems, Problems | image = Official_book_cover_art_for_Problems,_Problems,_Problems.jpg | caption = Official cover art for Volume 3, Grades 11-12 | books = | author = | editors = | title_orig = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = Canada | language = English and French | genre = non-fiction | discipline = | publisher = [[University of Waterloo]], Waterloo Mathematics Foundation | pub_date = | english_pub_date = | media_type = Print ([[paperback]]) | number_of_books = | list_books = | preceded by = | followed by = }} '''''Problems, Problems, Problems''''' is a series of educational mathematics textbooks ranging from grade 7-12. The math questions are from previous math contests held by the [[Centre for Education in Mathematics and Computing]] at the [[University of Waterloo]]. The series is a resource to complement the Canadian high school curriculum and for self-development, although it is also used to study for the CEMC Math Contests. Each combined grade level has several book volumes. Each book contains around 300 questions, and is categorized into various sections.<ref>{{cite web|title=CEMC University of Waterloo: Books and Posters|url=http://cemc.math.uwaterloo.ca/books.html|publisher=University of Waterloo|accessdate=21 December 2014 }}</ref> Each question has a reference number in the form "year-contest-question number".<ref>{{cite book|title=PROBLEMS, PROBLEMS, PROBLEMS Grades 11-12 Volume 3|isbn=978-0-921418-02-3|publisher=Waterloo Mathematics Foundation|date=April 1990}}</ref>
The ''Problems, Problems, Problems'' series collection is a [[National Library of Canada]] [[Cataloging in Publication]] (CIP).
